00:00:38.500 --> 00:00:41.000
Let's first begin with a simple example

00:00:41.100 --> 00:00:44.000
suppose you were tasked with recording the amount of customers

00:00:44.100 --> 00:00:46.500
that walk into a restaurant every hour

00:00:53.000 --> 00:00:55.500
At 2 p.m, there are 8 customers,

00:00:55.600 --> 00:00:57.500
at 3, there are 4,

00:00:57.600 --> 00:01:01.000
at 4 there are eleven and so on.

00:01:07.500 --> 00:01:10.300
The restaurant closes at 11 p.m, after which you

00:01:10.400 --> 00:01:13.800
tally up the total number of customers that came by to eat.

00:01:23.500 --> 00:01:25.500
You find that on Saturday for example,

00:01:25.600 --> 00:01:28.500
there were a total of 136 customers.

00:01:29.600 --> 00:01:33.600
